sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT team_id) 
FROM team_stages
WHERE stage_id = 301 AND position = 1;

SELECT AVG(home_shots_on_target) AS average_home_shots_on_target
FROM match_statistics
WHERE home_shots_on_target > (SELECT AVG(home_shots_on_target) FROM match_statistics);

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM matches 
WHERE group_name = 'UEFA CHAMPIONS LEAGUE - ROUND OF 16';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT team_id) 
FROM team_stages 
WHERE stage_id = 301;

external_knowledge:
- The "group stage" refers to the initial phase of a tournament where teams are divided into groups and play against each other;
- "Stage_id = 301" indicates a specific group stage in the tournament;
- The "top 3 teams" are those with the highest number of goals scored in the group stage.

- "shining stars" refers to teams that perform exceptionally well;
- "average number of goals scored" is calculated by summing the goals scored by all players in a team and dividing by the number of players;
- "more than 1" indicates a threshold for high performance.

- "shone the brightest" refers to the teams with the highest total points;
- "maintaining a strong average rank" refers to the average rank across all stages, where a lower rank number indicates better performance;
- "top 3 teams" means the teams with the highest total points and, in case of a tie, the best average rank.

